text:
And He replied: 
“Go and tell this people, ‘Be ever hearing, but never understanding; 
be ever seeing, but never perceiving.’

Manasseh devours Ephraim, and Ephraim Manasseh; 
together they turn against Judah. 
Despite all this, His anger is not turned away; His hand is still upraised.

For he says: 
‘By the strength of my hand I have done this, and by my wisdom, for I am clever. I have removed the boundaries of nations and plundered their treasures; 
like a mighty one I subdued their rulers.

For they hear: “Order on order, order on order, 
line on line, line on line; 
a little here, a little there.”

Then the word of the LORD to them will become: “Order on order, order on order, 
line on line, line on line; 
a little here, a little there,” so that they will go stumbling backward and will be injured, ensnared, and captured.

This is what the LORD says: 
“The products of Egypt and the merchandise of Cush, along with the Sabeans, men of stature, will come over to you and will be yours; they will trudge behind you; they will come over in chains and bow down to you. They will confess to you: ‘God is indeed with you, and there is no other; 
there is no other God.’”
